==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roustabout
<hw>Roust"a*bout`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A laborer, especially a deck hand, on a river
steamboat, who moves the cargo, loads and unloads wood, and the like; in
an opprobrious sense, a shiftless vagrant who lives by chance
jobs.</def> <mark>[Western U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rout</ent>⟦br⟧
